00:44:13.040 --> 00:44:14.340
&gt;&gt; Marilyn Chin: You felt that--

00:44:14.340 --> 00:44:15.640
you feel that the
language is different?

00:44:15.640 --> 00:44:17.320
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: The
languages seem so different

00:44:17.320 --> 00:44:18.620
in their construction.

00:44:18.620 --> 00:44:19.920
&gt;&gt; Marilyn Chin: Yeah, the--

00:44:19.920 --> 00:44:22.520
&gt;&gt; Ron Charles: How do you--
how do you translate that lesson

00:44:22.520 --> 00:44:25.110
of precision from
Chinese into English?

00:44:25.110 --> 00:44:27.550
&gt;&gt; Marilyn Chin: The-- you
know, Chinese-- I stud-- for--

00:44:27.550 --> 00:44:29.540
my undergraduate degree
was in Chinese poetry

00:44:29.540 --> 00:44:32.600
and I studied the Chinese
poem deeply and heavily,

00:44:32.600 --> 00:44:34.120
you know, I was really into it.

00:44:34.120 --> 00:44:36.400
I was such a nerd, right.

00:44:36.400 --> 00:44:38.460
But, you know, the Chi--

00:44:38.460 --> 00:44:43.720
classical Chinese poetry there's
no inflection or morphology.

00:44:43.720 --> 00:44:47.960
You-- I mean there-- there--
you know, there are no tenses,

00:44:47.960 --> 00:44:52.940
you know, no-- and, you
know, lack of case tense.

00:44:52.940 --> 00:44:56.370
I mean, and some poems there
aren't verbs, you know.

00:44:56.370 --> 00:45:00.460
I mean, I-- it's-- it's
so concise and precise

00:45:00.460 --> 00:45:05.290
and the imagery is so
precise that I try to bring

00:45:05.290 --> 00:45:08.250
that into the, you
know, my English poet--

00:45:08.250 --> 00:45:12.800
my writing, and t hat's,
I think-- I think that's--

00:45:12.800 --> 00:45:17.960
that's why I've been developing
a Chinese-American esthetics,

00:45:17.960 --> 00:45:21.640
a Chinese-American quatrain,
a Chinese-American poem,

00:45:21.640 --> 00:45:24.370
where I borrow from
the ancient Chinese--

00:45:24.370 --> 00:45:27.640
Chinese poetry and
try to bring--

00:45:27.640 --> 00:45:31.730
bring that precision into
the, you know, my-- so--

00:45:31.730 --> 00:45:33.390
you know, some of my poems.

00:45:33.390 --> 00:45:36.670
Now I write different kinds of
poems; I write long line poems

00:45:36.670 --> 00:45:39.900
and talky poems and-- and I--

00:45:39.900 --> 00:45:42.250
you know, some poems
