00:47:33.150 --> 00:47:37.040
and this is my-- one of my issue
poems about domestic violence,

00:47:37.040 --> 00:47:39.320
so, and these are
different vignettes of--

00:47:39.320 --> 00:47:41.110
these are vignettes
of different--

00:47:41.110 --> 00:47:46.100
different situations,
different families.

00:47:46.100 --> 00:47:50.700
Variations on an Ancient
Theme: The Drunken Husband.

00:47:50.700 --> 00:47:53.870
The dog is barking at the door.

00:47:53.870 --> 00:47:55.990
Daddy crashed the car.

00:47:55.990 --> 00:47:58.330
Hush, kids, go to your room.

00:47:58.330 --> 00:48:00.790
Don't come out until it's over.

00:48:00.790 --> 00:48:03.890
He stumbles in the
dim lit stairs,

00:48:03.890 --> 00:48:06.700
drops his Levi's to his ankles.

00:48:06.700 --> 00:48:09.100
Touch me and I'll
kill you she says,

00:48:09.100 --> 00:48:12.950
pointing a revolver at his head.

00:48:12.950 --> 00:48:16.290
The dog is barking at the door.

00:48:16.290 --> 00:48:19.140
She doesn't recognize
the master.

00:48:19.140 --> 00:48:24.400
She sniffs his guilty crotch,
positioned to bite it off.

00:48:24.400 --> 00:48:26.640
Jesus, control your dog.

00:48:26.640 --> 00:48:29.570
A man can't come
back to his castle.

00:48:29.570 --> 00:48:32.530
Kill him, Ling Ling, she sobs,

00:48:32.530 --> 00:48:36.250
curlers bobbing on
her shoulders.

00:48:36.250 --> 00:48:39.470
The dog is barking at the door.

00:48:39.470 --> 00:48:42.420
Quiet, Spot, let's not wake her.

00:48:42.420 --> 00:48:45.150
The bourbon is sour
on his breath.

00:48:45.150 --> 00:48:48.400
Lipstick on his proverbial
collar.

00:48:48.400 --> 00:48:51.330
He turns on the computer
in the den.

00:48:51.330 --> 00:48:53.970
He calms the dog with a bone.

00:48:53.970 --> 00:48:57.650
Upstairs she sleeps,
facing the wall,

00:48:57.650 --> 00:49:01.190
dreaming about the
perfume river.

00:49:01.190 --> 00:49:05.830
The dog is barking at the door.

00:49:05.830 --> 00:49:08.080
He stumbles in swinging.

00:49:08.080 --> 00:49:10.180
Where is my gook of a wife?

00:49:10.180 --> 00:49:13.300
Where are my half-breed
monsters?

00:49:13.300 --> 00:49:16.210
There is silence
up the cold stairs.

00:49:16.210 --> 00:49:18.920
No movement, no answer.

00:49:18.920 --> 00:49:21.820
The drawers are open
like graves.

00:49:21.820 --> 00:49:26.280
The closets agape
to the rafters.

00:49:26.280 --> 00:49:29.520
The dog is barking at the door.

00:49:29.520 --> 00:49:32.830
He stumbles in singing.

00:49:32.830 --> 00:49:35.100
How is my teenage bride?

00:49:35.100 --> 00:49:38.240
How is my mail-order darling?

00:49:38.240 --> 00:49:41.270
Perhaps she's pretending
to be asleep,

00:49:41.270 --> 00:49:44.510
waiting for her man's hard cock.

00:49:44.510 --> 00:49:47.120
He enters her from behind.

00:49:47.120 --> 00:49:50.860
